  "body": "This _might be_ a bug on `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.\n\nThe scenario is the following:\n1. The `message` state contains a default value\n2. Typing on the `<textarea>` _should_ overwrite the default value\n\nIt works as expected when not using `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, but when `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` is used, yes, it still works, but rather than replacing the state, it concatenates the default value with the values of `<textarea>`\n\nHere's the problematic example: http://jsfiddle.net/kb3gN/9185\n",
